<div id="container" style="height: 1354px">
	<div id="name" class="auto-style15" style="position: relative; left: 62px; top: 27px; width: 681px; height: 35px;">
		<h1 class="auto-style3" style="width: 705px">BETH&nbsp; HOUSTON&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
		<em>Poet, Author, 
		Educator</em></h1>
	</div>
	<div id="bio" style="position: relative; left: 292px; width: 500px; top: 84px; height: 247px;">
		<p class="auto-style17" style="margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:
normal">Beth Houston, MA, MFA, has taught creative writing, literature, and 
		composition at ten universities and colleges in California and Florida 
		and has worked as a writer and editor. She is a member of PEN 
		America-Professional and the Academy of American Poets, and has 
		published six poetry books, two nonfiction books, a novel, and over 
		two-hundred works in literary journals. Her provocative books on Deism 
		challenge prescribed beliefs with new thoughts about God, religion, 
		spirituality, science, politics, and creativity. Her blog includes ideas 
		&amp; opinions, literary criticism, interviews, and book discussion guides.</p>
	</div>
