		of the true poets, founders, religions, literatures, all ages have been, 
		and ever will be, our time and times to come, essentially the same—to 
		bring people back from their present strayings and sickly abstractions, 
		to the costless, average, divine, original concrete.”</span><span class="auto-style9" style="mso-spacerun:yes">&nbsp;
